<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-24T06:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-24T06:44:00-05:00" n="497" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.24/53: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-24T11:00:00-00:44">December
                                    24, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s telegram 312, December 4, 10 p.m. I have had a conversation
                            with President Barclay this morning for the first time in 3 weeks as he
                            has been confined to his bed. We discussed all pending matters which
                            will be taken up in individual telegrams.</p>
                        <p>The Liberian Government is still desirous of receiving lend-lease aid and
                            accordingly requests that the President’s certification of Liberia’s
                            eligibility be made public<note n="53" xml:id="d497fn53">For the public
                                statement regarding Lend-Lease aid to Liberia, see Department of
                                State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, January 16, 1943, p.
                                59.</note> in the usual way and that the Department proceed with the
                            preparation of a lend-lease agreement between the two countries.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>